  "response": "CPS typically refers to Child Protective Services, a government agency that investigates reports of child abuse or neglect. Without more specific context, I can provide some general information about their typical inner operations:\n\n1. Intake process\n- Receiving reports of potential child abuse/neglect\n- Initial screening of allegations\n- Determining if investigation is warranted\n\n2. Investigation procedures\n- Interviewing children, parents, and witnesses\n- Home visits\n- Assessing child safety\n- Documenting findings\n\n3. Case management\n- Evaluating risk levels\n- Developing safety plans\n- Determining potential interventions\n- Tracking case progress\n\n4. Potential actions\n- Providing family support services\n- Recommending counseling\n- Temporary child removal if deemed necessary\n- Working with legal system if required\n\n5. Staff roles\n- Social workers\n- Investigators\n- Case managers\n- Supervisors\n- Administrative support\n\nThese are general operational aspects. Specific procedures can vary by state and local jurisdiction.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
